snippet.textDisplay: I totally get the argument against China's wildlife agricultural industry on the basis of wildlife conservation, cross-species transmission, and outbreak prevention. But, I also understand that this very industry is the livelihood of a lot of people, and completely eradicating it would be very unfortunate for them. Is it reasonable at all to implement stricter regulation of health & safety standards for the farms raising these animals and the markets that sell them? Or would a law like this get ignored by the people in that industry regardless
